      "writtenOn": "2010-11-15T11:11:14Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "It\u0027d be nice to have a small description of what the AndroidConsoleClient does. E.g.\"\n\nAn AndroidConsoleClient object models a network connection to an Android console running on a QEMU emulator core. Use \"android_console_client_open()\" to connect, then use \"android_console_client_read/write\" to exchange messages with the core\u0027s console.\n\nThe main difference between an AndroidConsoleClient and a bare socket file descriptor is that all connect/read/write operations are performed with a timeout and can\u0027t block infinitely.",
      "revId": "42fe6c709273d6b62e31e1a0d7bde9e9124f9b45",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
